 results.\n\n- Sue Tetzlaff, The Employee Experience: A Capstone Guide to Peak Performance\n|\nAs you fight any war, sometimes the result may be defeat. Learn to be heroic even in your defeats.\n\n- Bangambiki Habyarimana, Book of Wisdom\n|\nWomen were different, no doubt about it. Men broke so much more quickly. Grief didn't break women. Instead it wore them down, it hollowed them out very slowly.\n\n- Cornelia Funke, Inkdeath\n|\nFrom my rotting body, flowers shall grow and I am in them, and that is eternity.\n\n- Edvard\n|\nIf you want to meet God ; ask yourself,Who lives in the sky?Why mountains grow high ? Why moon produce tides ?You'll find yourself in the lap of God.\n\n- Rajesh\n|\nFlowers don't tell, they show. That's the way good books should be too.'--Stephanie Skeem. Author of Flotsam\n\n- Stephanie\n|\nLearning to be a lady / is like learning / to live within a shell, / to be a crustacean encased / in a small white / uncomfortable world.\n\n- Stephanie Hemphill, Sisters of Glass\n|\nThe salvation of the species, lies in knowing the Self – it lies in contributing to the wellbeing of the Selves of others.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, Principia Humanitas\n|\nWith the rise of self- awareness, all separatisms cease to exist - all delusions cease to exist.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, Rowdy Buddha: The First Sapiens\n|\nAnd with a frenzied, frightened, anxious heart, she tumbled headfirst into the life she was destined to live.- Future\n\n- Abby Rosmarin, No One Reads Poetry: A Collection of Poems\n|\nPoverty should first be addressed in the mind because even if you give millions to a poor person, until there's a change of mindset, they will still remain the same.\n\n- Gift\n|\nIf you want to help anybody, go help people in need.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, Create Your Own Net Worth\n|\nThe main facts in human life are five: birth, food, sleep, love and death.\n\n- E.M.\n|\nAlive or dead, the truth won't rest. Rise up while you can.\n\n- Mira Grant, Feed\n|\nWriting means not just 